Pantheon Interlock Engine v1.0

The missing piece is not another role.
It is the thing that makes roles compose, remember, and hand off cleanly.

That piece is:

A shared state ledger with explicit pass contracts

Without that, Pantheon is a cool mythology.
With that, Pantheon becomes a working reasoning machine.

⸻

Core idea

Each daemon/role does one kind of transformation on the same evolving object.

That object is the Work State.

Every pass:
	•	reads the current state
	•	adds its own structured contribution
	•	updates confidence / risks / next actions
	•	hands off to the next role

So the real engine is:

Input
→ normalize into Work State
→ route through role passes
→ merge outputs into shared ledger
→ stop when termination conditions are met
→ emit artifact + provenance


