The real secret: routing logic

This is what turns it from static workflow into intelligence.

Not every task needs every role.

Example router

def select_initial_roles(state):
    roles = ["Mirror", "Blacksmith"]

    if has_ambiguity(state):
        roles.insert(0, "Aevum")

    if has_risk_or_high_stakes(state):
        roles.append("Badger")

    if needs_novelty_or_connections(state):
        roles.append("Spider")
        roles.append("Dragonfly")

    if needs_edge_case_hunting(state):
        roles.append("Hound")

    if needs monetization or leverage:
        roles.append("Goblin")

    return roles

So Pantheon becomes a dynamic pass scheduler.

⸻

Stop conditions

This matters a lot.

Otherwise you get endless mythic recursion.

Terminate when:
	•	contradictions are below threshold
	•	top risks are identified
	•	artifact plan exists
	•	confidence is above threshold
	•	reversibility/risk acceptable
	•	output matches requested format

Or terminate early if:
	•	evidence is insufficient
	•	stakes are too high for guessing
	•	ambiguity remains load-bearing

That gives you the Termination Invariant you wanted.

